5. Key Technical Insights (So Far)
5.1 GPS Velocity is Extremely Valuable

GPS velocity measurements are extremely accurate.

They can assist:

heading validation

ground track estimation

energy calculations

5.2 Gravity-Vector Assumptions Break in Turns

Many attitude systems assume acceleration is dominated by gravity.

During coordinated turns, centripetal acceleration corrupts this assumption.

Better models may use:

yaw rate

GPS velocity

turn geometry

5.3 Instrumentation Should Emphasize Meaning

Sensors provide data.

Pilots need understanding.

Instrumentation should interpret sensor data into useful flight awareness.

6. AI Collaboration Lessons

AI tools (ChatGPT, Codex) are highly effective at:

generating infrastructure code

implementing communication protocols

building software scaffolding

debugging patterns

AI tools are less effective at:

system architecture

aviation physics

operational flight understanding

validation of sensor assumptions

Therefore:

Human domain expertise must guide development.

7. Constraints

Several architectural rules apply.

Logging Priority

Flight data logging must never block or fail.

Telemetry and networking are secondary.

Debug Visibility

Systems must remain observable through serial debug output.

Deterministic Processing

Flight computer tasks must not depend on networking performance.

